I am a researcher at the Department of Library Science of Carlos III University of Madrid. I'm a member of the Laboratory of Information Metric Studies (LEMI) and the Research Institute for Higher Education and Science (INAECU). 

My current work concerns the study of epistemic injustices in science, with a focus on African academic publishing. My doctoral work conceptualizes epistemic injsutice in scince and studies certain types using bibliometric methods.

I participate in several projects at the regional, national and european level and collaborate with colleagues at the UC3M, UAM, CWTS (Leiden University), and CREST (Stellenbosch University)

